<div id="review_55873913" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/55873913" />
    <a title="Elizabeth (Alaska)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2026178-elizabeth-alaska"><img alt="Elizabeth (Alaska)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1304966095p2/2026178.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/55873913?book_show_action=true">May 12, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elizabeth (Alaska)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elizabeth (Alaska)" href="/user/show/2026178-elizabeth-alaska">Elizabeth (Alaska)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=5-star-reads">5-star-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=awards-pulitzer">awards-pulitzer</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2026178-elizabeth-alaska?shelf=author-stegner-wallace">author-stegner-wallace</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer55873913" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer410157036996423493">As I read this, I thought, &quot;this is about a 4 star read.&quot; So why did I give it 5 stars? It is such a beautiful book, that&apos;s why. There were many parts that didn&apos;t seem to move along, which is why I thought I would be stingy, but I&apos;m so very glad the author took his time. And I felt myself talking to the characters, mostly Susan. &quot;Don&apos;t be so removed from your life - how many do you get?&quot; Could I be so involved with a story and <i>not</i> give it 5 stars? </span>
  <span id="freeText410157036996423493" style="display:none">As I read this, I thought, "this is about a 4 star read." So why did I give it 5 stars? It is such a beautiful book, that's why. There were many parts that didn't seem to move along, which is why I thought I would be stingy, but I'm so very glad the author took his time. And I felt myself talking to the characters, mostly Susan. "Don't be so removed from your life - how many do you get?" Could I be so involved with a story and <i>not</i> give it 5 stars? </span>
